<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-11-23T07:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-11-23T07:24:00-05:00" n="314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d314">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60 p 31/30: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-11-23T14:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">November 23,
                                        1925—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 23—10:49
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>96. My telegram number 95, November 17, 4 p.m., also despatch number
                            3262, October 10th.<note n="21" xml:id="d314fn21">Neither
                                printed.</note> Has Department any objection to including Finland
                            among list of countries excluded from operation provisional trade
                            agreement? If no objection, I assume I still have authority to sign text
                            submitted by Department in telegram 42, August 23, 2 p.m., 1924, and
                            number 39, August 4, 3 p.m., this year. I am advised agreement is likely
                            now and to be signed here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>